OL,3,CColour and music at Wrexham's first
OL,4,CAfrican Caribbean festival
OL,6,F"With the incidents that have happened
OL,7,Fa few weeks ago people were scared but
OL,8,Fwhat is happening now is that people
OL,9,Fare sitting and chatting with their
OL,10,Fneighbours. I think it is giving
OL,11,FAfricans hope that Wales and Wrexham
OL,12,Fis for them. It's opening doors."
OL,14,FLisinayte Lopes from Wrexham's Palops
OL,15,FUnited CIC, said the event would bring
OL,16,Fpeople together.
OL,18,FShe explained that Palops United CIC
OL,19,Fwas created to support people from
OL,20,FAfrican Communities where Portuguese
OL,21,Fis the first language.
